[
    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "22 Lecture 22: Order finding"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                121,
                581,
                146
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "This is an application of the phase estimation algorithm, important for the factorization algorithm. Consider two integers, x and N , with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x < N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and no common factors."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                157,
                857,
                207
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Definition: the order of x modulo N is the smallest positive integer r such that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x ^ { r } \\equiv 1 { \\pmod { N } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                220,
                855,
                258
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The problem of finding the order is a di\u0000cult problem for a classical computer: no classical polynomial algorithm is known. By this we mean an algorithm polynomial in the number L of bits necessary to specify the problem, for example the number of bits necessary for the binary expression of N . Thus L satisfies "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N \\leq 2 ^ { L }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                269,
                858,
                339
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Exercise: find the order of 5 modulo 21"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                352,
                527,
                369
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Theorem: r always exists (provided x and N are coprime) and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r \\leq N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". For the proof, see the Appendix."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                382,
                858,
                416
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "22.1 The algorithm"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                438,
                393,
                459
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The quantum algorithm for order finding is simply the algorithm for phase estimation applied to a unitary operator "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "defined by"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                467,
                857,
                502
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "U _ {x, N} | y \\rangle \\equiv | x y \\bmod N \\rangle \\tag {22.1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/ed6261f14bc9522539d5194432ae5826dea35bccd35602a1193f640d7e1ef7b0.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                401,
                516,
                853,
                534
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where y is a L-bit integer, thus "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 \\leq y \\leq 2 ^ { L } - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "acts on a vector space of dimension "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "2 ^ { L }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                546,
                858,
                581
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Technical note: when "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "y \\geq N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the application "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is defined to act on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| y \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "as the identity. Thus "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "acts nontrivially on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| y \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "only for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 \\leq y \\leq N - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                593,
                858,
                631
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Theorem: the states defined by"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                642,
                458,
                659
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left| u _ {s} \\right\\rangle \\equiv \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {k = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {- 2 \\pi i s k}{r} \\right] \\left| x ^ {k} \\bmod N \\right\\rangle \\tag {22.2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/bdf133204b5e144d4ee7bdc5a7387d8a8f1fee8cd99f1ee05b4e141a22290e2b.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                322,
                674,
                855,
                719
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with integer s satisfying "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 ~ \\leq ~ s ~ \\leq ~ r - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(and r = order of x modulo "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", are eigenstates of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ":"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                730,
                857,
                764
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "U _ {x, N} | u _ {s} \\rangle = \\exp \\left[ \\frac {2 \\pi i s}{r} \\right] | u _ {s} \\rangle \\tag {22.3}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/8dcbab9c6d7f3d9c26c505d0615d742414db104efaa1cf0f38c7e3d3a9df93e6.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                383,
                764,
                853,
                801
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Applying now the phase estimation algorithm gives an estimation the phase "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "of the eigenvalue "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\exp [ 2 \\pi i s / r ]"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and from "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "we can deduce r (via the continued fraction algorithm, see later), i.e. the order of x modulo N ."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                806,
                857,
                858
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "108"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                482,
                906,
                515,
                919
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Proof:"
                    }
                ],
                "level": 2
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                125,
                236,
                140
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\begin{array}{l} U _ {x, N} | u _ {s} \\rangle = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {k = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {- 2 \\pi i s k}{r} \\right] | x ^ {k + 1} \\bmod N \\rangle \\\\ = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {k = 1} ^ {r} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {- 2 \\pi i s (k - 1)}{r} \\right] | x ^ {k} \\bmod {\\mathrm{N}} \\rangle \\\\ = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {k = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {- 2 \\pi i s (k - 1)}{r} \\right] | x ^ {k} \\bmod \\mathrm{N} \\rangle \\\\ = \\exp \\left[ \\frac {2 \\pi i s}{r} \\right] \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {k = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {- 2 \\pi i s k}{r} \\right] | x ^ {k} \\bmod N \\rangle \\\\ = \\exp \\left[ \\frac {2 \\pi i s}{r} \\right] | u _ {s} \\rangle \\tag {22.4} \\\\ \\end{array}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/9ca7ee657839fd365fba37545a2e06afe2b182132739fc7d7e2a190b622c3af7.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                268,
                148,
                855,
                376
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "We redefined "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k  k - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in the sum in the second line, and in the third line we wrote the sum from "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "as a sum from "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = r - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "since both the exponent and the vector "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\vert x ^ { k } \\mathrm { m o d ~ N } \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "do not change if "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k  k + r ,"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "so that the term with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is equal to the term with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Indeed the exponent remains the same since "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\exp [ 2 \\pi i \\times i n t e g e r ] = 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| x ^ { k }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "mod "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathrm { N } \\rangle = | x ^ { k + r }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "mod N<sub>i</sub> because "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x ^ { r } \\equiv 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "mod N."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                381,
                855,
                482
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Exercise: prove that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U _ { x , N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is unitary."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                169,
                498,
                499,
                515
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "For the phase estimation algorithm, we need to know the eigenstate "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| u _ { s } \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", but this is equivalent to know the order r (since it enters the definition (22.2) of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\left| u _ { s } \\right. )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which is just the number we want to find ! There is a way out of this logical loop: we can choose as second register the state "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| 1 \\rangle = | 0 0 . . . 0 1 \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", where all the L qubits are set to 0 except the last one which is set to 1 . This state is in fact a sum of eigenstates "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\left| u _ { s } \\right."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ":"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                528,
                858,
                631
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "| 1 \\rangle = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {s = 0} ^ {r - 1} | u _ {s} \\rangle \\tag {22.5}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/c6779500b5331e10bf33d2f934e4e9bbba08e36d6d0fb9aa9e29aeb71d22ece2.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                423,
                631,
                853,
                675
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "as can be seen from the inversion of formula (22.2):"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                680,
                588,
                697
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left| x ^ {k} \\bmod \\mathrm{N} \\right\\rangle = \\frac {1}{\\sqrt {r}} \\sum_ {s = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp \\left[ \\frac {2 \\pi i s k}{r} \\right] \\left| u _ {s} \\right\\rangle \\tag {22.6}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/80b226ebf903cb7765bd4157911eea7ade0a0c9c9e0d0f9d12fefac9eb706682.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                332,
                706,
                855,
                750
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "by taking "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". The inversion formula can be verified easily noting that"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                757,
                773,
                774
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sum_ {s = 0} ^ {r - 1} \\exp [ - 2 \\pi i s k / r ] = r \\delta_ {k, 0} \\tag {22.7}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/d82ff2b197e54d76a86c6372c89379fb0183e2820f616766b7ee8cb506b881a3.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                386,
                783,
                853,
                826
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "this relation is trivial, for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k \\neq 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "use the formula for the geometric sum). Another way of proving (22.6) is to notice that the transformation matrix of (22.2) is unitary, and its inverse is given by its transpose conjugate."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                834,
                855,
                887
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "109"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                482,
                906,
                515,
                919
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "In summary, taking as the input of the second register the state "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| 1 \\rangle"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the algorithm will estimate a phase "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", where s can take the values "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 \\leq s \\leq r - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with equal probabilities "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", but r is fixed to be the order of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "modulo "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". We now need a procedure to extract "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "if we know that it is the denominator of a rational number "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". This procedure is the continued fraction algorithm we describe in next Section."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                125,
                858,
                213
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Note: one possible result of the algorithm is that the estimated phase is zero, since "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s = 0 \\to s / r = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "may happen with probability "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 / r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". One has then to repeat the algorithm until one finds a nonvanishing phase."
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                225,
                858,
                279
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "110"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                482,
                904,
                515,
                920
            ]
        }
    ]
]